.TH "alloc_tty_buffer" 9 "alloc_tty_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_tty_buffer \- Return a new struct iucv_tty_buffer element.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct iucv_tty_buffer *" alloc_tty_buffer
.BI "(size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
Size of the internal buffer used to store data.
.IP "flags" 12
Memory allocation flags passed to mempool.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates a new struct iucv_tty_buffer element and, optionally,
allocates an internal data buffer with the specified size \fIsize\fP.
The internal data buffer is always allocated with GFP_DMA which is
required for receiving and sending data with IUCV.
.SH "NOTE"
The total message size arises from the internal buffer size and the
members of the iucv_tty_msg structure.
The function returns NULL if memory allocation has failed.
